question:
What is printed by the following code?

@FunctionalInterface
interface Calc {
    int calc(int x);
}

Calc c = (int x) -> x * x;
System.out.println(c.calc(5));

What is printed by the following code?

@FunctionalInterface
interface StringFunc {
    String func(String str);
}

StringFunc one = (str) -> str + "111";
System.out.println(one.func("Hello"));

What is printed by the following code?

Consumer<String> c1 = s -> System.out.println("Hello " + s);
Consumer<String> c2 = s -> System.out.println("Welcome!");
Consumer<String> combined = c1.andThen(c2);
combined.accept("George");

What is printed by the following code?

ArrayList<Integer> al = new ArrayList<>();
al.add(100); al.add(200); al.add(50);
al.forEach(num -> System.out.print(num * 2 + " "));

What is printed by the following code?

List<Integer> number = Arrays.asList(2, 3, 4, 5);
List<Integer> result = number.stream().map(x -> x + 2).collect(Collectors.toList());
System.out.println(result);

What is printed by the following code?

List<String> names = Arrays.asList("Madona", "Avi", "Shadi");
List<String> result = names.stream().filter(str -> str.startsWith("A")).collect(Collectors.toList());
System.out.println(result);

What is printed by the following code?

List<Integer> number = Arrays.asList(40, 35, 7, 10);
int sum = number.stream().filter(x -> x > 30).reduce(0, (ans, element) -> ans + element);
System.out.println(sum);

What is printed by the following code?

List<String> names = Arrays.asList("a", "bb", "ccc");
names.forEach(System.out::println);

What is printed by the following code?

Function<String, Integer> strLength = s -> s.length();
System.out.println(strLength.apply("hello"));

What is printed by the following code?

Predicate<Integer> isEven = n -> n % 2 == 0;
System.out.println(isEven.test(4));
System.out.println(isEven.test(7));

What is printed by the following code?

Supplier<String> s = () -> "Hello, world!";
System.out.println(s.get());
